HEADWORD: Gavage
<hw>Ga`vage"</hw> <pr>(g⟦adot⟧`v⟦adot⟧zh")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., fr. <ets>gaver</ets> to gorge.]</ety> <def>Forced feeding (as
of poultry or infants) by means of a tube passed through the mouth down
to the stomach.</def>⟦br⟧
